column98:
I will give time and money to the causes which have the highest marginal utility given my goals. Though, one of my goals is financial security for myself. Rarely do my goals equate to traditional "charity," but rather in altering the trajectory and speed of progress.

I also sometimes think my ability to influence the world is less than I imagine, and the consequences of my actions are too unpredictable, so I tend to sympathize very much with Adam Smith's Theory of Moral Sentiments.
